rComments: No idea how his rating is so low on here. He is a super smart, articulate, and caring prof! Great lectures, explained the material very well, and always encouraged us to ask questions if something wasn't clear. Always responded quickly to emails. He even was flexible with an assignment deadline. Would definitely recommend taking a class with him!

Professor Forge encourages students to participate every class. Although his midterms are challenging, he wants you to ask questions and answers as many times as you need. He is there if you need to visit his office hours. Monotone prof, so make sure you try and participate to make it more exciting and engaging. Make sure you understand the content
The class is very boring and the homework was so tough, you have to buy Stata to finished your homework which is difficult, the midterm is totally hard, hope you can drop this class

Unfortunately one of the professors I've disliked the most during my Econ Bachelors. He's currently finishing his PhD and clearly does not want to teach this class. His lectures are extremely dry and he shows no enthousiasm yet expects students to participate all the time. Would recommend to AVOID this guy. No wonder people don't show up...
